The paper presents a method for estimating node importance in knowledge graphs using graph neural networks (GNNs), which involves supervised machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses downstream applications such as item recommendation and resource allocation, which suggests relevance to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper deals with real-world KGs with different characteristics, indicating relevance to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
